Switch camera to follow entity.

# Input Parameters
* [input:Player_Entity] (Entity) - Entity of player to switch the camera for.
* [input:Follow_Entity] (Entity) - Entity to follow with the camera. Must have an "Object Camera" component.
* [input:Camera_Template_Name] (String) - Name of the object camera, as specified in the "Object Camera" component.

# Usage
Starting in Luna VI, craftperson can configure the camera to follow an entity.
This allows finer control over the position of the camera and its movement.
Use this node to start following an entity with the camera.
See "Example" section below to see how to configure an object camera.

# Example
First, create an object camera from the "Manage Main Camera" panel.
For this example, we name it `Koko's Cinematic Camera`.
[image:set_player_camera_to_follow_entity_configure_camera]
Next, create an "Object Camera" component on the entity that you want camera to follow.
For this example, we selected the camera we created above
and then named this object camera `Koko's Cinematic Camera for Ball`.
[image:set_player_camera_to_follow_entity_configure_component]
Lastly, a node graph is created to switch the camera to the object camera.
[image:set_player_camera_to_follow_entity_example]

# Notes
* If [input:Player_Entity] is not a player entity,
  this node raises "Entity does not exist" error
  (can be misleading, because the entity may exist)
  but continues the execution.
* If [input:Follow_Entity] does not exist, this node is no-op.
* If [input:Follow_Entity] does not have an "Object Camera" component
  or [input:Camera_Template_Name] is not a name of an object camera specified in the component,
  this node is no-op.

# Performance
This node took ~8 units to run on average.

